crest migration","Somite formation","Notochord development"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003Eventral neural tube patterning\u003C/strong\u003E. Sonic hedgehog protein is secreted by the notochord and establishes a concentration gradient from ventral to dorsal regions of the developing neural tube. This gradient induces specific cell types including floor plate cells and motor neurons in a concentration-dependent manner.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDorsal neural tube specification\u003C/strong\u003E - This is controlled by bone morphogenetic proteins secreted from the roof plate, not Sonic hedgehog\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENeural crest migration\u003C/strong\u003E - While Sonic hedgehog influences neural crest cells, their migration is primarily controlled by other factors\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESomite formation\u003C/strong\u003E - This process is regulated by other pathways including the Notch-Delta signalling system\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENotochord development\u003C/strong\u003E - The notochord secretes Sonic hedgehog but its own development is not dependent on this protein\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESonic hedgehog also plays crucial roles in limb development, establishing anterior-posterior patterning of digits. Disruption of Sonic hedgehog signalling can lead to severe developmental abnormalities including holoprosencephaly and limb malformations.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Sonic hedgehog protein establishes ventral-dorsal patterning in the developing neural tube through concentration gradients","Sonic hedgehog signalling from the notochord induces floor plate formation and ventral neural cell types","Sonic hedgehog is essential for proper development of the central nervous 